title: For Sale:  1 of a kind DPMS AR-10 7.62/.308 Tiger Stripe
postcontent:
I set out with a project in mind and I think it turned out far better than I had planned.

I began with a brand new in box DPMS Oracle RFLR-OC, a 16" 1:10 twist barrel, an A3 style flat top upper with forward assist and dust cover, and a 20 round magazine.

I removed the factory hand guards, pistol grip, collapsible stock, gas block, and buffer.

I media blasted all the parkerization with Aluminum Oxide, soaked everything in degreaser, then gas treated it to remove the oils, then repeated the degreasing process until nothing came out of the parts.

I upgraded the handguard to a 12" J.P. Enterprises free float and the factory gas block to a Troy Industries low profile gas block. The stock was upgraded to a VLTOR E-MOD and the grip to a CAA Mako 6-piece interchangeable for individual fit. The buffer was upgraded to a heavy buffer to absorb additional recoil.

All parts were then individually Cerakoted in Graphite Black and Burnt Bronze with the receiver getting a custom tiger striping, and oven cured. This is the most reliable and wear resistant finish you can get.

What you have is now an accurized, virtually maintenance free AR-10 that will turn heads everywhere you go.

Price for the rifle is $2200. Optics and mount were only put on for illustration and are not included. The rifle remains unfired. I am an individual collector, and this is from my personal collection.

Contact me at REDACTED.

title: For Sale:  S&W 1911PD Gunsite edition 45 ACP
postcontent:
This is the increasingly difficult to find Smith & Wesson 1911PD Gunsite Edition pistol. 

The lusterous blueing on the slide, barrel and other hard parts is nicely contrasted by the lovely walnut stocks with the carved S&W and Gunsite Raven logo's which is echoed in the Raven engraving on the receiver. The frame is made from Scandium. The sights are Novak low rise and make for a smooth, no snag draw from a holster (no front gold bead). The barrel is 4 1/4" with a match grade barrel bushing. The trigger is adjustable. The gun comes in the factory lockable protective case with the original manual, barrel wrench, 2 S&W OEM ACT made, 8 round magazines and sealed packet containing the sample factory fired casing. 

I am the original owner and have fired this very accurate pistol less than 100 rounds of Federal and RP 45 ACP hardball. The earlier manufactured pistols like this one (SN FSP 0798) were completely hand fitted for maximum accuracy and reliability. The gun is in completely stock, unmodified condition since new. I will offer approximately 2 and 1/2 boxes of new RP (2 boxes of 50 rounds 230gr RN, approximately 1/2 box of Federal 230gr RN) to the buyer at my cost from about a year ago.

I play by the rules. For sale face to face only to bonafide Arkansas resident with proof of Ar residency, otherwise it has to go through (or sale to) an FFL. 

I also believe in describing an item accurately. Feel free to check my feedback on ebay (handle- achildofthesky )I am an individual and not a dealer or business and because of this, the gun is sold with out warranties of any type on my part and all sales are final. That said, if you have been looking for a truely nice example of these accurate and finely assembled and increasingly hard to find pistols you will not be dissapointed with this one. I have a couple of other high quality collectable guns I will be selling to help generate funds for a home purchase.
